{"id":"gera","term":"Gera","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Grain. (1.) The son of Bela and grandson of Benjamin (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:3\">1 Chr. 8:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:5\">5</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:7\">7</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The father of Ehud the judge (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 3:15\">Judg. 3:15</a>).</p>\n<p>(3.) The father of Shimei, who so grossly abused David (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 16:5\">2 Sam. 16:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 19:16\">19:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 19:18\">18</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 8:3","1 Chronicles 8:5","1 Chronicles 8:7","Judges 3:15","2 Samuel 16:5","2 Samuel 19:16","2 Samuel 19:18"]}